.TH DSMR-EMAIL-ADMIN 8 "2026" "dsmr-email-admin 1.0" "DSMR mail stack"
.SH NAME
dsmr-email-admin \- health check and repair for the DSMR mail stack
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dsmr-email-admin
.I command
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dsmr-email-admin
audits and repairs a DSMR qmail/vpopmail/dovecot mail host.  It targets the
faults that recur when a control or configuration file predates a packaging
fix: a postinst that only creates a file when absent never repairs an existing
one on upgrade, so a host first provisioned before the fix keeps the old value.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B check
Read-only health check across packages, services, the PostgreSQL backend,
dovecot authentication, the qmail-smtpd softlimit, relay rules, and listening
ports.  Exits non-zero if any check fails.
.TP
.B fix \fR[\fB--dry-run\fR] [\fITARGET\fR...]
Repair detected issues.  Each fix runs only when its detector fires, and backs
up the file it changes as \fI<file>.bak-<timestamp>\fR.  Targets:
.RS
.TP
.B softlimit
Raise \fI/var/lib/qmail/control/softlimit\fR to 100000000 when it is lower,
then restart qmail-smtpd and qmail-submission.  qmail-smtpd links OpenSSL and
krb5 and fails to start under a low address-space cap.
.TP
.B pgsql-config
Swap the password and database fields of \fI/home/vpopmail/etc/vpopmail.pgsql\fR
when they are reversed, then regenerate the dovecot SQL conf.
.TP
.B dovecot-sql
Regenerate \fI/etc/dovecot/dovecot-vpopmail-sql.conf.ext\fR from vpopmail.pgsql
and reload dovecot.
.TP
.B pg-cluster
Start and enable the PostgreSQL cluster on the port vpopmail uses.
.RE
.IP
With no target, every detected issue is fixed.
.TP
.B selftest \fR[\fIDOMAIN\fR]
Create a throwaway vpopmail mailbox, inject a message, confirm delivery and
dovecot authentication, then remove the mailbox.
.TP
.B version \fR|\fB help
Print version or usage.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /home/vpopmail/etc/vpopmail.pgsql
vpopmail PostgreSQL connection (host|port|user|password|database).
.TP
.I /var/lib/qmail/control/softlimit
Address-space cap applied to qmail-smtpd and qmail-submission.
.TP
.I /etc/dovecot/dovecot-vpopmail-sql.conf.ext
dovecot PostgreSQL connection, derived from vpopmail.pgsql.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dsmr-smtpauth (8),
.BR qmailctl (8)
